In React how can I get Button in a parent component to dispatch a function onClick in multiple child components?In React, you can use the onClick property on a button in a parent component and pass a callback function that will be called when the button is clicked. This callback function can then be passed as a prop to multiple child components, where it can be invoked when the child components' elements are clicked.Here's an example:Copy code// Parent component
function Parent() {
  const handleClick = () => {
    console.log('Button was clicked');
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
      <Child1 onClick={handleClick} />
      <Child2 onClick={handleClick} />
    </div>
  );
}

