In this way, when the button within the EditMenu component is clicked, it will invoke the handleSave function that was passed as a prop from the EditMenuContainer component, which will perform the logic you've defined in the function.Is there a way to get the handleSave function to be invoked in the EditMenu child component only when the button is pressed in the Parent component? So there is no button in the child components only in the parent component?Yes, there are a few ways to achieve this behavior. One way is to have the child component listen for an event that is emitted from the parent component when the button is clicked.Here is one example using event listeners :Copy code// Parent component
function Parent() {
    const handleSave = (changes) => {
        console.log("Save changes:"+changes);
